notesStmt.note: Folios 113-118 originally belonged to another manuscript of about the same date.
Maimon ben Se῾adya᾿ ben Mosheh Al-Musa᾿i (patron): inscribed, folio 110v.
Folios 111-112: a calendar for the 286th and 287th cycle, followed by the series of prognostications based on the date of the teḳufot.
Folios 113-118: originally a part of another manuscript: several poetical pieces and additional blessings.
Folios 119r-123r: originally belonging to a different manuscript of approximately 18th century: additional prayers.
Folios 123v-124r: a table with a 292th cycle.
Folio 2r: partly illegible piece similar to Kol nidre.
Folio 4r: an additional prayer and the beginning of Kol nidre.
Zekhariah ben Daṿid: inscribed with his name in a note, folio 1v.
Folio 124r: two records of sale, dated 1797 and 1811 respectively.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: A service book according to the Yemenite rite.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 2; ruled lines: 30; written lines: 30; Uniform layout. Visible mastara ruling. Initial words written in larger characters. Leaf catchwords on every verso. Numerous marginal notes and additions.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite semi-cursive script, punctuated, of the 17th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Prayer Book. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2390.'
